title: What Trump (and the GOP) can’t do
text: “Govern.” It’s the loneliest verb in Washington. To attempt to govern is to run the risk of being called a sell-out. To govern — to pass laws, treaties, tax plans, budgets — almost invariably requires compromise in a country as polarized politically as the U.S. But as my colleague Karen Tumulty (among others) reports today, […] ...
